ratings.rComments: Javid hands out treats for correct answers in class, it kept students like me engaged in the lecture. He makes funny jokes and narrate anecdotes, they kept the mood of the classroom lively and entertaining.  Lectures were very thorough given the fact that there were so much material to cover in a short amount of time.

By far my favorite professor yet. I really hate to see him leave UIUC  because I was hoping to sign up for his calc II class again. Everything in the class was pretty much perfect and made calculus very enjoyable.

Take notes at lectures and do the practice tests that he sends you and you should get at least a B. People with AP credit will still find this course as a nice refresher.

Great
